nts1.n: Chicken Foot Soup w/ Goya Gumbani and Dom P
nts1.d: London-based jazz artist Goya Gumbani stops by to share heartfelt picks from his collection.
West London songwriter and vocalist Arlo Parks comes through with an hour of music and stories – club music and current favourites.
The eclectic and diverse frequencies from a true East Bay Area native, Abby Imperial is ready to bring the soulful sounds of Rnb, g-funk, deep house, jungle & more..

nts1.n: DRUM POETRY w/ Dev/Null: Vibration Center Atmospheric Jungle Set
nts1.d:
Drum & bass and jungle every month with Equinox & Dev/Null.
From the host: "Drum Poetry is back this month with an all-vinyl & dubplate atmospheric set played by Dev/Null at Vibration Centre LA last November."
Moesha 13 is an artist and curator of Malian origin based in Marseille. She was unanimously selected as artist of the year 2020 on SHAPE Platform (Sound, Heterogeneous Art and Performance in Europe).
Certified veteran grime DJ Grandmixxer raises hell on Thursday nights, either rolling solo or with guest MCs in the hot-seat. Tune in once a month for the latest…

‘When we refuse… we create dissonance and more importantly, we allow dissonance to continue.’ - from Jack Halberstam’s introduction to the Undercommons.
Disruptive music for broken times curated by Nymity. Queering, Unlearning, Fragments and Imaginings.
Artwork by Harry King

Mexican record label, Naafi, settle in at NTS for a showcase of the weirdest experimentations in club culture that have bubbled to the surface of Soundcloud. Dazed rhythms converging into Jersey stutters, and tumblr-era trap for two straight hours on a Monday.

Artist and audio maker, Alicia Matthews, takes over the NTS airwaves once a month for a rhythm ’n’ gloom showdown.
Past projects include SUE ZUKI (Domestic Exile/ NTS), LAPS (MIC Records/ DFA Records) and Organs of  Love (Optimo Music).

A monthly transmission of displaced rock n roll, exotic punk and early electronics, paying favor to all things primitive and sleazy. LA visual artist Amanda Siegel delves into the international underground, offering a thorough sonic survey of protopunk, hard rock, synthpunk, powerpop, psych, industrial and more.

nts1.d: First thing on Fridays - Jack Rollo's here to take care of things.

nts2.n: COMO LA FLOR w/ Jazmin: FLOR DE JAMAICA
nts2.d:
Música sentimental for all the sad girls and sad boys.
From the host: "Buenos Dias. New Nuevo Como La Flor to honor my first photo book being published, FLOR DE JAMAICA; bridging my dream worlds/women/ and flowers with the perfect soundtrack.  
Would u watch the movie to this soundscape?? 
Coming soon to a cinema …… in my dreams and yours."

nts2.n: Tragic Magic w/ Julianna Barwick and Mary Lattimore
nts2.d: The celebrated composers Julianna Barwick & Mary Lattimore come together for Tragic Magic - their latest collaborative release. Heralded by three special guest radio shows recorded from our LA studio.

Where the wall meets the floor, Temporal Cove is a body of sound exploring the ethereal and ephemeral. Smilegoth dives into shoegaze, post-rock, house and more to articulate a flow of reverberations that can be felt on every surface.
From the host: _"smilegoth invites legendary American rock band Pavement to Temporal Cove for a guest mix + interview. A 10 minute conversation with Bob and Mark, from an hour and a half interview by smilegoth and untitled (halo)." _
"The sun is made of plastic or elastic, I don't know which"
Lesser heard sounds with a focus on femmes in punk from artist and musician Sara A.

LA event series, Moony Habits, Alex Ho takes over - live from our Los Angeles studio.
From the host: "Sandie Shaw's in the House…!!! Just moved into a new place.. tidy'd up the studio and pulled records I haven't heard in a while. I had fun recording.. hope you enjoy the listen :)"

nts2.n: UNITED IN FLAMES W/ VICKIE CHERIE & MALIBU
nts2.d:
Malibu is a French electronic musician whose work sails between ambient and ethereal music.
Forever inspired by soft reverbed vocals and melodious chord progressions, Malibu’s music is an immersive nostalgic journey in a sea of synthetic strings and choirs.

The Bones-led independent hip hop collective and label TeamSESH take the NTS airwaves for a monthly one hour transmission live from our LA studio.
From the host: "The first TeamSesh NTS Radio broadcast of 2026 is once more curated by hnrk: Featuring a blend of various styles and (sub-)genres, unreleased tunes, new musical discoveries and releases from TeamSesh members as well as peers and friends."
Label head Michael Lundy explores Rap Vacation’s experimental influences, with guests and exclusive cuts from the thriving LA beat scene.
Prestonian singer songwriter Rainy Miller presents the progress check, a bi-monthly show playing an hour of archived experiments and influences.

nts2.n: THEY ARE GUTTING A BODY OF WATER (R)
nts2.d: Philadelphia cult property and experimental shoegazers They Are Gutting A Body Of Water present an hour of handpicked music, narrative diversions and fourth wall breaks.

Welcome to LXXXVIII – the ninth Actress album to be created by Darren Cunningham and the very first presentation of Actress’ voyage into luxury sonics.
A lifetime in the making, LXXXVIII is the culmination of 25 years’ honing mind-shorting, soul-igniting audio
infusions for dance floors, rave dens, festivals, and concert hall, and the inaugural vessel for Actress’ cruise into novel strata of artistic influence: the executive suites, yacht decks and private jets of our planet’s ultimate power players.

subtle.d: With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!

XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Vinyl DJ from Leigh-on-Sea. Loves collecting records with a wide array of taste ranging from House and Techno to Grime, Dubstep and Jungle. Garage holds a special place in his heart and makes up the largest part of my collection and DJ sets.

DJ & Producer hailing from Watford influenced by Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Grime with releases on NSX records & Ghost Phone, spinning electronic genres from R&B edits, Drum and Bass and everything in between.
Highlander brings you 2 hours of the freshest Jungle, Hardcore, Dubstep and Breaks. 3rd Saturday 7-9pm lock in!

subtle.n: What's The Weather, Selecta? w/ Megan Wroe

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.n: Daddy Differently and Dirty Dave - Things of Life
dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
